list.name: Fix function that picks surface atoms for nanorod.
list.comment:
Modifies Nanoparticle class to allow a LigandInfo: ligand_num dict to be passed. This ensures proper assign of specific LigandType objects to PlaceholderTypes.
Also updates scripts that generate AMBER atom types with antechamber and writes correct .mol2 files. Automatic backup of REDS .mol2 and overwrite option.

task.summary: Default task
Fix sporadic bug in minimium_index assignment

Beginning of refactoring to consolidate functions between modules. Also, extend functionality for future projects. New Modules: -geometry_tools -script_writing_tools
Also renaming functions and variables to be more informative and explicitly state each variable's type (eg. numpy array, list, tuple)
Moved most functions to new, separate module for writing Leap scripts. Still need to clean up the main script writing function for cluster-builder.

Uses new function (geometry_tools.get_surface_index) to identify surface atoms based on their coordination number instead of on distance from center. Previous method overestimated number of surface atoms and therefore bonded ligands to bulk atoms. This should reduce strain on systems during minimization and MD.

Finally fixes duplicate bond writing caused by bonding [surface, core] and [core, surface]. This update sorted indices before adding to index_pairs_tuple (nice, but not essential) and check for existing bond before passing nearest_neighbor_index_list to choose_from_neighbors function in geometry_tools (fix).
Next step is to implement check in script_writing_tools to avoid (warn if necessary) for function script.
Fixes problems with cluster_builder and supporing modules. Adds free_ligand_builder (meant to build systems with physisorbed ligands). Still needs work. Corrects issues with AMBER input files
Updates input files.

Script for save every 10th frame with all atoms and saving every frame of solute-only.
Automatically deletes original trajectory, after checking that output files exist.
Fixes problems with cluster_builder and supporing modules. Adds free_ligand_builder (meant to build systems with physisorbed ligands). Still needs work. Corrects issues with AMBER input files
Backup save.
Backup save.
Renames variable more descriptive, switches to fprint, and checks for existing frcmod file.
Absorbs atomtype.sh script and incorporates the call to antechamber into existing loop.
Backup save.

Only includes AMBER input files.
Removed unnecessary parameters (eg. vrandom, which only applies for Andersen thermostatting.
Increased coupling constants for heat and equil1 steps to make for more natural heat trajectory. Velocities will be moderated by the harmonic restraints.
Reorganizes files to place all ligand-specific scripts in the same directory.

Improves script for running amber. Adds command line control of loop type (folder or .prmtop based), run type(full md, prod run, or vacuum minimization). Also adds checking for input files. Fixes globbing error that results in creation of */ directory, etc.

Creates cpu_minimize functions that run PME minimization. Modifies job_runner function to first call cpu_minimize, wait for completion, then call amber, and run next minimization. This prevents too many jobs running on the CPU and slowing down pmemd runs. Fixes typo in vacmin (cpptaj to cpptraj).
Adds support for glob pattern with -p argument. Changes all echo commands to printf for robustness (hopefully). Adds text output when .rst7 file is not found and run is terminated.
Fix function that picks surface atoms for nanorod.

task.summary: Fixes nearest neighbor finding function to work with 2-D Numpy arrays coordinates contained in 3D matrix of unit cells. Only compares distances with atoms in adjacent unit cells instead of the entire nanorod.

Creates Classes for Atoms, UnitCells, NPSuperLattice(just a nanoparticle), LigandType, Ligand, and System(tLeap).
Backup for trying to correct inheritance of Ligand from parent LigandType when specifying a particular LigandType.

Fixes numerous function in nanorod_builder, NanoParticle, and script_writing_object that improve nanoparticle building in tLeap. Primarily it creates classes for "generic" NPs and atoms that allow for placement of ligands, without specifying type. "Specific" NPs and atoms are separate classes when ligand types are specified.
Also fixes method for placing ligands so that they are spread evenly on the surface.

Modifies Nanoparticle class to allow a LigandInfo: ligand_num dict to be passed. This ensures proper assign of specific LigandType objects to PlaceholderTypes.
Also updates scripts that generate AMBER atom types with antechamber and writes correct .mol2 files. Automatic backup of REDS .mol2 and overwrite option.
Bash script for generating tLeap input that loads FFs and solvates/salts mol2 files.
Renamed script (leaptotalbuilder.py) for generating nanorods.
Updates classes used to create nanoparticles, ligands, and leap systems (NanoParticle.py) and functions for writing tLeap scripts using those classes(script_writing_object.py).
